    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1958-06-16T23:45:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1958-06-16T23:45:00-05:00" n="89"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d89">
                <head>89. Telegram From the Chief of Naval Operations (<persName corresp="#p_BAAA1"
                        type="from">Burke</persName>) to the Commander in Chief, United States Naval
                    Forces, Eastern Atlantic and Mediterranean (<persName corresp="#p_HAJLJ1"
                        type="to">Holloway</persName>)<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d89fn1"
                        >Source: Washington National Records Center, RG 330, OASD/ISA Files: <gloss
                            target="#t_FRC1">FRC</gloss> 62 A 1698, 092 Lebanon TS Sensitive. Top
                        Secret; Emergency. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_BAAA1">Burke</persName>.
                        Also sent to COMSIXFLT, COMDESRON 36. Repeated to Alusna Beirut, U.S.S. <hi
                            rend="italic">Rich</hi>, and U.S.S. <hi rend="italic">New</hi>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1958-06-17T00:45:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 17, 1958—12:45 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>170545Z. Lebanon situation deteriorating. State has received dispatch<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d89fn2">
                        <ref target="#d88">
                            <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>
                        </ref>.</note> from American Ambassador Beirut request from <persName
                        corresp="#p_CC7">Chamoun</persName> for assistance.</p>
                <pb facs="0177" n="145" xml:id="pg_145"/>
                <p>Keep 2 <gloss target="#t_DD1">DD</gloss> within 25 miles but over horizon and out
                    of sight from Beirut. These 2 <gloss target="#t_DD1">DD</gloss> be prepared
                    enter Beirut harbor and land small landing force to evacuate American citizens
                    or furnish assistance when requested by American Ambassador by radio direct to
                    destroyers.</p>
                <p>Beirut dispatch and State’s reply on the way.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BAAA1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Burke</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
